description: Teachers union boss Randi Weingarten recalled the SPLC comparing school choice advocates to segregationists during a podcast episode released on Tuesday.

title: Brazilian prosecutor believed Danelo Cavalcante escaped Pennsylvania prison to face charge in 'lenient' Brazil
description: The Brazilian prosecutor over Danelo Calvacante's homicide case in Tocantins thought the convicted killer facing life in a U.S. prison was escaping to face a lighter sentence in Brazil.

title: Spain leads way with task force as governments rush to regulate AI
description: A new policy task force will establish a framework through which Spain can develop and implement its use of artificial intelligence technologies across all sectors.

title: 'America's Got Talent' judge Howie Mandel explains why he's 'embracing AI'
description: "America's Got Talent" judge Howie Mandel isn't afraid of artificial intelligence, and is already happily working with the technology.

title: Prince Willliam, Kate Middleton's 'passion' is key to their success: Queen Rania of Jordan
description: Britain's Prince and Princess of Wales made a surprise visit to Jordan in June to witness the nuptials of Crown Prince Hussein and Princess Rajwa.

title: Bibbidi-bobbidi-boo, Disney is through... and we won't let it destroy our kids any more
description: Disney, the company that was once beloved for wholesome, family-friendly content has changed. Look at what's happening with beloved classics like "The Little Mermaid" and "Snow White."

title: Artificial intelligence helps doctors predict patients’ risk of dying, study finds: ‘Sense of urgency’
description: Researchers at OSF HealthCare in Illinois are using artificial intelligence to help physicians determine which patients have a higher chance of dying during a hospital stay. Here's how.

title: GREG GUTFELD: Ultra-liberal WaPo columnist David Ignatius is throwing in the security blanket
description: FOX News host Greg Gutfeld reacts to Washington Post columnist David Ignatius saying President Biden is too old to run for re-election on "Gutfeld!"

title: On this day in history, September 15, 1981, Sandra Day O'Connor approved for SCOTUS by Senate committee
description: On this day in history, Sept. 15, 1981, Sandra Day O'Connor's nomination to the Supreme Court was approved by the Senate Judiciary Committee. She became the first woman on the high court.
